        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001270_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><p rend=" no-indent"><space extent="4" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="small gray" hand="#U"><metamark/><!-- circle around 9 -->9 41</add></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><date when="1858-03-06"><subst><del>5</del><add place="over-text">6</add></subst> March 1858</date>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName><settlement type="town">Birkenhead</settlement></placeName> 
<lb/><persName>Bevan Braithwaite<choice><abbr>Esq</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice></persName></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Friend,</p><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><p>I enclose a note
<lb/>from <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Tidman</persName> and
<lb/>an answer which if
<lb/>you see no objection
<lb/>to I shall trouble you
<lb/>to forward. I also send
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> John Moffat</persName>'s
<lb/>letter in reference to it
<lb/>If you think it better not
<lb/>to send the letter burn it

	<pb facs="liv_001270_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>I have kept no copy</p>
<lb/><p><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">s</hi> Wilbraham Taylor</persName>
<lb/>went to <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Tidman</persName>
<lb/>about the other or pecuniary
<lb/>matter and as you will
<lb/>see by an enclosure
<lb/>from him that is
<lb/>satisfactorily arranged
<lb/><unclear>I wished</unclear> a writing but
<lb/>they take care to do the
<lb/>opposite of what
<lb/><term type="occupation">lawyers</term> are liable too
<lb/>they are very chary of
<lb/>words on paper

	<pb facs="liv_001270_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>you need not return either
<lb/>of these. I am off on
<lb/><choice><sic>monday</sic><corr>Monday</corr></choice> forenoon - the
<lb/>Pearl is out of dock
<lb/>with the Launch on
<lb/>board. It pleases us
<lb/>better than we expected</p>
<lb/><p>I advised <persName>John</persName> to
<lb/>make a distinction between
<lb/>the men in power and
<lb/>the Society itself - It is
<lb/>not unlikely but that
<lb/>after I am gone they may
<lb/>utter insinuations <unclear>against</unclear>

	<pb facs="liv_001270_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>I am not conscious of any one
<lb/>thing that can be brought up
<lb/>against me but should
<lb/>there be and especially in the
<lb/>"<bibl>British Banner</bibl>" which is
<lb/>in the hands of <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Tidman</persName> &amp;c
<lb/>I should like to know of it
<lb/>and if you thought it advisable
<lb/>would answer it. In the
<lb/>mean time I commit my 
<lb/>way into the Lord &amp; trust he
<lb/>will guide me as he has
<lb/>done. I shall think over the
<lb/>matter of your notes</p>
<lb/><p>In the meanwhile
<lb/>may every blessing be on 
<lb/>you &amp; yours
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>

            </div>
